{"id":"2212.01604","submitter":"Taras Banakh","authors":"Taras Banakh and Andriy Rega","title":"Polyboundedness of zero-closed semigroups","comments":"16 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR math.GN math.LO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The polyboundedness number $\\mathrm{cov}(\\mathcal A_X)$ of a semigroup $X$ is\nthe smallest cardinality of a cover of $X$ by sets of the form $\\{x\\in\nX:a_0xa_1\\cdots xa_n=b\\}$ for some $n\\ge 1$, $b\\in X$ and $a_0,\\dots,a_n\\in\nX^1=X\\cup\\{1\\}$. Semigroups with finite polyboundedness number are called\npolybounded. A semigroup $X$ is called zero-closed if $X$ is closed in its\n$0$-extension $X^0=\\{0\\}\\cup X$ endowed with any Hausdorff semigroup topology.\nWe prove that any zero-closed infinite semigroup $X$ has $\\mathrm{cov}(\\mathcal\nA_X)<|X|$. Under Martin's Axiom, a zero-closed semigroup is polybounded if $X$\nadmits a compact Hausdorff semigroup topology or $X$ has a separable complete\nsubinvariant metric.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Dec 2022 12:20:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-06"}
