 greater than $\\pi$. As the\ngap ratio reduces, the widening of the lock-in region is accompanied by the\nwidening of the IInd response branch and a narrowing down of the Ist response\nbranch. For the gap ratio of g/D = 0.1, the Ist branch vanishes entirely. This\nwork is directly relevant to the design, maintenance, and fatigue life\nestimation of underwater pipelines/cables laid on the seabed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Dec 2022 15:14:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-06"}
